==Useful Info==
'''Wolf spiders''' are one of the simpler arachnids, but also one of the most durable and vicious. They can keep up with hasted players, have far more [[HP]] than most spiders, and pack a painful, [[poison]]ous bite that can tear up a low-on-mana caster quickly. Even worse, while they may be encountered alone, they also appear in large groups with other spider varieties. They can occasionally be found in [[the Dungeon]] and [[the Vaults]], and are very common in the [[Spider's Nest]].

==Tips & Tricks==
*Although poison resistance will mostly prevent their bites from poisoning you, they still do heavy damage. Decent [[AC]] and [[EV]] are strongly recommended.
*Like most bugs, wolf spiders are vulnerable to poison. [[Mephitic Cloud]]ing a crowd of them should create a lot of dead spiders very quickly.
*[[Ignite Poison]] also works well, especially since you'll probably be fighting a few other kinds of spiders at the same time.

